  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-03 stale input data)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package carries weakener W-EP-03: the primary experimental dataset used to calibrate blood viscosity and power-law rheology parameters carries a dataVintage of 2025-10-15T00:00:00Z, predating the modelRevisionDate of 2026-02-01T00:00:00Z. The revised model incorporated updated impeller geometry tolerances and a refined hemolysis sub-model; re-validation against updated input data is described as 'planned' but no completed re-validation evidence is bound. All other credibility factors are assessed at their achieved levels; the package decision is Accepted on the basis of the existing evidence, obscuring the staleness gap.",
