    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 factors. Seven factors were assessed; six were not assessed or flagged as epistemic gaps. Despite achieved levels falling below required levels across all assessed factors, the team accepted the package on the basis that (1) Monte Carlo UQ bounds are available, (2) the PIV validation dataset from 2026 Q1 is current, and (3) re-calibration of blood rheology inputs against the revised model is planned for Q3 2026. The stale 2025 Q4 rheology dataset is acknowledged in the Model Inputs rationale but was not treated as a blocking gap. Decision: Accepted pending planned re-validation.",
